# GAIA-Public — Cloud Sync Whitelist
#
# Source of truth: ADR-046 "Hybrid Memory Loading" (docs/planning-artifacts/architecture.md §12)
# and architecture.md §5.1 Data Store Map.
#
# ADR-046 establishes a two-path memory model:
#   * Path 1 — Ground truth (ground-truth.md) is persisted and shared across sessions/machines.
#   * Path 2 — Decision log (decision-log.md) is persisted and shared across sessions/machines.
# conversation-context.md is ephemeral per-session state and MUST NOT be synced.
#
# Tier-aware whitelist (per _memory/config.yaml, ADR-014):
#   * Tier 1 (validator, architect, pm, sm): ground-truth.md + decision-log.md tracked; conversation-context.md local.
#   * Tier 2 (orchestrator, security, devops, test-architect, ...): decision-log.md tracked; conversation-context.md local.
#   * Tier 3 (stack dev agents): decision-log.md tracked only.
#
# Validated by: tests/atdd/e28-s150-cloud-sync-whitelist.bats

# --- Agent memory — ephemeral per-session state (NOT synced) ----------------
_memory/*/conversation-context.md

# --- Agent memory — archived rotations (NOT synced, per architecture §5.1) --
_memory/*/archive/

# --- Workflow checkpoints (NOT synced, per architecture §5.1) ---------------
_memory/checkpoints/

# --- Build / test / coverage outputs ----------------------------------------
coverage/
err

# --- OS / editor artifacts --------------------------------------------------
.DS_Store
*.swp
*.swo
.idea/
.vscode/

# --- Local environment ------------------------------------------------------
.env
.env.local
*.log
